---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

export const prerender = true

const surfaces = [
  {
    title: 'CLI',
    price: '$0',
    body: 'Draft, schedule, inspect, and publish posts from your terminal.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Local MCP server',
    price: '$0',
    body: 'Give Claude, Codex, Cursor, and other MCP clients the same ilo tools.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Agent skill',
    price: '$0',
    body: 'Teach coding agents the ilo workflow and publishing confirmation rules.',
  },
]
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Pricing"
  description="ilo is a free and open source CLI, local MCP server, and agent skill for drafting, scheduling, and publishing social posts."
>
  <main class="site-frame py-16">
    <section class="max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-primary">MIT licensed</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-pretty text-4xl font-medium -tracking-[0.6px] text-foreground">
        Use every ilo surface for free.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-pretty text-xl/8 text-foreground-muted">
        Install the CLI, add the local MCP server to your agent, and install the
        ilo skill. The full project is open source under the MIT license.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 grid gap-3 md:grid-cols-3">
      {surfaces.map((item) => (
        <article class="rounded-lg bg-muted p-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-foreground-muted">{item.title}</p>
          <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground">{item.price}</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">{item.body}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </section>

    <section class="mt-14 max-w-2xl border-t border-border pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-foreground">Start with the CLI</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
        <p>
          The CLI is the quickest way to set up ilo and see how it works. Run
          <code>ilo start</code> to configure X publishing, then create a draft
          with <code>ilo drafts create</code>. Drafts and schedules are stored in
          a local SQLite database.
        </p>
        <p>
          Scheduling accepts ISO timestamps and phrases such as
          <code>tomorrow at 9am</code> or <code>Friday at 2pm</code>. Run the
          scheduler once from a task runner or leave it watching for due posts.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-medium text-foreground">Add ilo to an agent</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
        <p>
          The local MCP server exposes ilo's draft, schedule, status, and
          publishing tools to compatible agents. The CLI and MCP server use the
          same drafts and settings, so you can move between them without copying
          work around.
        </p>
        <p>
          Install the packaged skill with <code>ilo skill install</code>. The
          skill tells an agent which ilo tool to use and makes the confirmation
          rule explicit. Creating and scheduling drafts is safe to do directly.
          Publishing still requires approval for the exact post.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-medium text-foreground">Bring X API access</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
        Publishing uses an X developer app that you configure during setup. X
        controls its developer plans, usage limits, and charges. ilo does not
        add a fee to those provider costs.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-medium text-foreground">
        Use ilo for your own posts or client work
      </h2>
      <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
        <p>
          Start with the public profile and posts you want to understand. The
          research tools and report guides help an agent inspect strong posts,
          weak posts, topics, hooks, formats, timing, and audience response. Ask
          it to show the evidence behind each recommendation before you turn a
          finding into a draft.
        </p>
        <p>
          The same process works for a client review or competitor research.
          Record the handle, date range, sample size, and posts behind the
          findings so the result can be checked later. Keep each profile's
          evidence separate. Comparing two tidy samples beats mixing a dozen
          accounts into one vague content brief.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-medium text-foreground">Use and change the source</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
        <p>
          The MIT license allows personal and commercial use, modification, and
          redistribution. The repository contains the CLI, MCP server, skill,
          documentation, and tests. You can add another provider, change the
          workflow, or use the core packages in your own project.
        </p>
        <p>
          Contributions are welcome. Bug reports, documentation fixes, and
          tested provider work all help. If ilo saves you time, you can also
          sponsor ongoing maintenance.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a
          class="inline-flex h-10 items-center rounded-lg bg-primary px-5 text-sm font-medium text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary-hover"
          href="https://github.com/iannuttall/ilo"
        >
          View on GitHub
        </a>
        <a
          class="inline-flex h-10 items-center rounded-lg bg-secondary px-5 text-sm font-medium text-secondary-foreground hover:bg-secondary-hover"
          href="https://github.com/sponsors/iannuttall"
        >
          Sponsor
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
